There are three complications for people with type 1 diabetes:
- a long-term, one involving several systems due to persistently high blood glucose;
- a short-term, keto-acidosis, due to the lack of enough insulin;
- an emergency, hypoglycemia, due to a drop in glucose levels, due to a lack of glucose intake and hepatic glycogen reserve, with insulin active.
Excessively restricting carbohydrates can lead to the latter situation, a serious and potentially fatal emergency.
Those who use insulin should not go on low carb or keto diets, otherwise they will run serious risks ...
